## Event Records

The first field of every record is the event type.

Records delivered on /event (agent-side events only):

  turn_start  FS  <session-uuid>  FS  <model>
  thinking    FS  <text>
  text        FS  <text>
  tool_start  FS  <name>  FS  <tool-call-id>  FS  <argv[0]>  FS  <argv[1]>  ...
  tool_end    FS  <ok|err>  FS  <full-output>
  turn_end    FS  <end_turn|aborted|error>
  error       FS  <message>
  model       FS  <new-model-name>
  session_new FS  <new-session-uuid>

Additional records written only to the session file (inputs, not agent events):

  session  FS  <uuid>  FS  <model>  FS  <unix-timestamp>   ← file header record
  prompt   FS  <text>                                       ← user message sent
  steer    FS  <text>                                       ← steering message sent

Notes:
  - tool_start has a variable number of fields: type, name, id, then one field
    per argv element.  No quoting or joining needed; each element is its own field.
  - text and thinking records carry individual delta chunks as they arrive from
    the SSE stream.  On session replay, consecutive text records are concatenated
    to reconstruct the full response.
  - tool_end carries the full exec output — no truncation for the session file.
    For the live /event stream the same full output is delivered.
  - prompt and steer records are NOT emitted on /event; they record inputs and
    belong only in the session file.

