## Concurrency Model

Three procs communicate via channels.  No select/epoll anywhere.

  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  Main proc  (9P srv loop)                                        │
  │  threadpostmountsrv → lib9p dispatch                             │
  │                                                                  │
  │  on /message clunk:   send(reqchan, AgentReq{PROMPT, text})      │
  │  on /steer clunk:     send(reqchan, AgentReq{STEER, text})       │
  │  on /ctl "abort":     send(abortchan, 1)                         │
  │  on /output fsread:   park Req* in pending_output                │
  │  on /event  fsread:   park Req* in pending_event                 │
  │  on outchan recv:     respond(pending_output)                    │
  │  on eventchan recv:   respond(pending_event)                     │
  └──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘
                             │ reqchan (AgentReq*)
                             ▼
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  Agent proc                                                      │
  │  recv(reqchan) → write_session(prompt/steer, ...)                │
  │  check token expiry → refresh if needed                          │
  │  iodial HTTP conn → tlsClient                                    │
  │  write Anthropic request → Brdline SSE loop                      │
  │  on thinking_delta:  emit_event + write_session("thinking",...)  │
  │  on text_delta:      send(outchan, chunk)                        │
  │                      emit_event + write_session("text",...)      │
  │  on tool_use:        emit_event + write_session("tool_start",...) │
  │                      threadspawn exec child, collect output      │
  │                      emit_event + write_session("tool_end",...)  │
  │                      loop back to API with tool result           │
  │  on end_turn:        send(outchan, "[done]
") then nil          │
  │                      emit_event + write_session("turn_end",...)  │
  │                      Bflush(session_bio)                         │
  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                             ↑ authchan (token string)
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  Auth proc                                                       │
  │  startup: load ~/lib/9ai/token or run OAuth device-code flow     │
  │  send initial token on authchan                                  │
  │  iosleep loop: refresh ~5 min before expiry                      │
  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  abortchan: main → agent

